title: For Sale:  1930's Commercial Colt M1911A1
location: Tampa Bay Area, Tampa/St. Pete, Florida
postcontent: A very rare commercial Colt 1911A1, made in Hartford, Connecticut in about 1933.  It is believed to be one of 5,320 pistols made for the Argentinean police and used  for about 70 years before Sarco imported it back to the USA,   where it was born.   During its time in the Policia Federale, this pistol  was undoubtedly used during Argentina's many revolutions and decades of political upheaval as evidenced by heavy use.   If only it could talk!   This particular pistol has had the disconnector and sear replaced by Wood Bros.   The originals that came with it are included. Included with this pistol is the original sear and disconnector,   set of Pachmeyer grips, Navidrex Mahogany grips, and a 50 round box Federal ammo.   As you can see, this pistol has been through a great deal of history but still functions great!   Made in America with the Colt pony still legible!  A special treasure for the serious collector!  Asking $950. Buyer must sign a Bill of Sale and must present a Florida Driver License or State I.D. Cash only. Not interested in trades.Source:  Charles Clawson's book Colt .45 Government Models (Commercial Series) page 143.
